.page-header
  %h2 How to get your arrest information
%p In order to apply for juvenile expungement, you will need your arrest information.
%br/
%h3
  If you were arrested in Chicago:
%p
  You can pick up your arrest record
  %strong for free
  in person at:
  %br/
  = succeed "Records" do
    %br/
  and Services Division of the Chicago Police Department
  %br/
  3510 S Michigan, Chicago IL 60653
  %br>/
  (312)745-5508
  %br>/
  Mon-Fri 8am-12pm
%br/
%h3
  If you were arrested outside of Chicago:
%p
  You will need to get two pieces of information from the police department that arrested you: (1) the date of arrest and (2) the arrest charge. Call the police department where you were arrested, and ask how you can get this information.
  %br/
  = succeed "If" do
    %br/
  a police department tells you it cannot give you this information, contact the Juvenile Expungement Help Desk at 312-229-6359.
%br/
%br/
.well.well-sm
  After you have your arrest information, move on to the next step -
  = succeed "!" do
    %a{:href => "/step3"} applying for expungement
